# PII / secret scanner allowlist
#
# One Python regex per line. Matches against either:
#   * the offending substring (e.g., "example@example.com"), or
#   * the file path of the staged change.
# A match suppresses the corresponding finding from scripts/hooks/check_pii.py.
#
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored.

# --- Documentation example addresses (RFC 2606) ---------------------------
example\.com$
example\.org$
example\.net$
@example\.com\b
@example\.org\b
@example\.net\b

# --- Common public sample / placeholder values ----------------------------
test@test\.com
foo@bar\.com
user@host
your[\.\-_]?email@
contact@geopinning\.space
support@geopinning\.space

# --- Public corporate emails / domains used as references in the content --
# (Add as needed, e.g. press@toyota.co.jp if cited in industry/ pages.)

# --- Repo-internal example data files --------------------------------------
# Allow any sample/dummy content under tests/fixtures/
^tests/fixtures/

# --- Postal codes and 12-digit numbers used in pure data contexts ---------
# Most stat-card numerics (e.g., production volumes) are 12 digits when grouped
# with commas removed. Suppress only when clearly tabular numeric prose.
# Example: 「生産能力 約120,000,000台/年」→ "120000000000" if comma-stripped.
^src/content/industry/

# --- Wikimedia attribution image URLs (no PII risk) ----------------------
upload\.wikimedia\.org
commons\.wikimedia\.org
